to mutate the genes,

266
00:19:47,729 --> 00:19:52,234
I can create a being who's
more powerful than him,

267
00:19:52,734 --> 00:19:55,737
Who has total
allegiance to me.

268
00:20:04,246 --> 00:20:05,747
You better
stand back.

269
00:20:06,248 --> 00:20:08,250
Keep your eye out.

270
00:20:37,696 --> 00:20:39,698
You wanted
to see me?

271
00:20:39,698 --> 00:20:42,701
Yeah, hi, Clark.
Please, come in.

272
00:20:42,701 --> 00:20:45,704
I've come up with
a brilliant idea.

273
00:20:45,704 --> 00:20:47,206
Oh...really?

274
00:20:47,206 --> 00:20:49,208
Well, daddy thinks
it's brilliant.

275
00:20:49,208 --> 00:20:51,210
You'll write this new series

276
00:20:51,210 --> 00:20:53,212
Called Metropolis after hours.

277
00:20:53,212 --> 00:20:55,214
Who, me? I...

278
00:20:55,214 --> 00:20:57,216
It's wonderful.

279
00:20:57,216 --> 00:20:59,218
It's great,
isn't it?

280
00:20:59,218 --> 00:21:01,220
I'm not
right for this.

281
00:21:01,220 --> 00:21:03,222
You're perfect
for it.

282
00:21:03,222 --> 00:21:04,223
You're young,

283
00:21:04,223 --> 00:21:06,225
You're single,
you're successful.

284
00:21:06,225 --> 00:21:08,727
I'm usually
in bed by 10:30.

285
00:21:08,727 --> 00:21:11,230
That's just it.
You don't flaunt it.

286
00:21:11,230 --> 00:21:13,732
You're no slave
to fashion, although...

287
00:21:13,732 --> 00:21:15,734
Have you considered 
using contacts?

288
00:21:16,235 --> 00:21:18,737
Uh, they, uh,
make my eyes itch.

289
00:21:18,737 --> 00:21:22,741
Listen, I thought we
could do this together.

290
00:21:22,741 --> 00:21:25,244
I know all
the right places.

291
00:21:25,244 --> 00:21:27,746
I belong
to the right clubs.

292
00:21:27,746 --> 00:21:29,748
We'll start tonight
at the metro club.

293
00:21:30,249 --> 00:21:31,250
Oh, tonight?

294
00:21:31,250 --> 00:21:32,751
Yeah. It's a date.

295
00:21:32,751 --> 00:21:34,253
A date?

296
00:21:34,253 --> 00:21:35,254
A date?

297
00:21:35,254 --> 00:21:37,756
Uh, well, it's just 
business, actually.

298
00:21:37,756 --> 00:21:41,760
I've got a letter
for Superman, care of me.

299
00:21:41,760 --> 00:21:43,762
Superman
gets mail here?

300
00:21:43,762 --> 00:21:46,265
It's probably just
a picture request.

301
00:21:46,265 --> 00:21:47,266
I could look after
it for you, lois.

302
00:21:47,766 --> 00:21:49,768
I think it's more
than a fan letter.

303
00:21:49,768 --> 00:21:51,770
I think you
should read it.

304
00:21:51,770 --> 00:21:55,274
"Dear Superman,
my teacher is speaking

305
00:21:55,274 --> 00:21:57,276
"About the president's
speech on the arms race.

306
00:21:57,276 --> 00:22:01,780
"We're all
very unhappy about it,

307
00:22:01,780 --> 00:22:04,283
"And I said
we should get Superman

308
00:22:04,783 --> 00:22:06,285
"To rid the world
of nuclear arms

309
00:22:06,285 --> 00:22:09,788
Because only
he could do it."

310
00:22:12,291 --> 00:22:14,793
"Everybody thinks
I'm a space cadet.

311
00:22:14,793 --> 00:22:16,295
"Once you've destroyed
all nuclear missiles,

312
00:22:16,295 --> 00:22:17,296
"They'll see
I was right.

313
00:22:17,296 --> 00:22:18,297
"Superman can make sure

314
00:22:18,297 --> 00:22:19,798
"We don't blow
ourselves up.

315
00:22:20,299 --> 00:22:22,801
"Thanks a lot. I know
you'll come through.

316
00:22:22,801 --> 00:22:24,803
Your friend, jeremy."

317
00:22:24,803 --> 00:22:25,804
Poor kid.

318
00:22:25,804 --> 00:22:28,307
I'll get back to work.

319
00:22:28,307 --> 00:22:30,309
There's an angle
in this.

320
00:22:30,309 --> 00:22:32,311
An angle?
He's just a kid!

321
00:22:32,311 --> 00:22:34,313
Daddy loves whipping
up campaigns,

322
00:22:34,313 --> 00:22:36,315
And the public
loves it!

323
00:22:36,315 --> 00:22:38,317
Lacy!

324
00:22:38,317 --> 00:22:40,319
We're going to make
this kid a celebrity.

325
00:22:40,319 --> 00:22:42,321
Everybody in the world
will wonder

326
00:22:42,321 --> 00:22:44,823
What Superman's 
reply is.

327
00:22:48,327 --> 00:22:50,329
Welcome to
Metropolis, jeremy.

328
00:22:50,329 --> 00:22:51,830
I'm Mr. Warfield,

329
00:22:52,331 --> 00:22:53,832
And this is
my daughter lacy.

330
00:22:54,333 --> 00:22:54,833
Hi, jeremy.

331
00:22:55,334 --> 00:22:56,835
Now come along
and meet the press.

332
00:22:56,835 --> 00:22:57,836
Have a good trip?

333
00:22:58,337 --> 00:22:59,338
Car had a flat.

334
00:22:59,338 --> 00:23:00,839
Oh, I'm sorry
to hear that.

335
00:23:00,839 --> 00:23:04,343
Here, let everybody
get a picture of you.

336
00:23:04,343 --> 00:23:05,344
That's it, everyone.

337
00:23:05,344 --> 00:23:06,345
Jeremy, over here.

338
00:23:06,345 --> 00:23:07,846
What a boy!

339
00:23:07,846 --> 00:23:08,847
Now, come along,

340
00:23:08,847 --> 00:23:12,351
And tell the American public
what you told me.

341
00:23:12,851 --> 00:23:15,854
I said I wish Superman
would've said yes!

342
00:23:15,854 --> 00:23:16,855
Did you get that?

343
00:23:16,855 --> 00:23:17,856
Man: no, we didn't.

344
00:23:17,856 --> 00:23:18,857
Say it again...

345
00:23:19,358 --> 00:23:20,359
Loudly.

346
00:23:20,359 --> 00:23:23,862
I said I wish Superman
would've said yes.

347
00:23:31,370 --> 00:23:33,872
Miss lane. Miss lane.

348
00:23:33,872 --> 00:23:35,374
Take a look at this.

349
00:23:35,374 --> 00:23:37,376
Hot off the press.

350
00:23:37,376 --> 00:23:38,877
Oh, my god!

351
00:23:38,877 --> 00:23:41,380
This time, he's
gone too far.

352
00:23:41,380 --> 00:23:43,382
Look, Clark.

353
00:23:43,382 --> 00:23:45,384
Can't wait for
the chief's reaction.

354
00:23:45,384 --> 00:23:48,887
I'm through
taking it lying down!

355
00:23:48,887 --> 00:23:50,889
Anybody wants me,
I'll be downtown!

356
00:23:50,889 --> 00:23:53,392
Chief look
different to you?

357
00:23:53,392 --> 00:23:57,396
He looks like my father 
asking for a loan.

358
00:23:57,396 --> 00:23:59,898
I'll make sure
he's all right.

359
00:23:59,898 --> 00:24:00,899
Look, Clark,

360
00:24:00,899 --> 00:24:03,402
There's nothing
we can do about it.

361
00:24:03,402 --> 00:24:05,404
It's Superman's
decision now.

362
00:24:05,404 --> 00:24:07,406
I'm sure he'll do
the right thing.

363
00:24:45,944 --> 00:24:49,948
May the elders
watch over you, my son.

364
00:24:51,950 --> 00:24:54,953
Their wisdom
is all that is left

365
00:24:54,953 --> 00:24:57,956
Of a once powerful
and enlightened planet.

366
00:24:59,458 --> 00:25:02,961
You must listen
to them, Kal-El.

367
00:25:04,963 --> 00:25:06,465
Listen.

368
00:25:10,969 --> 00:25:13,472
I know I'm forbidden
to interfere,

369
00:25:13,472 --> 00:25:15,974
And yet the earth
is threatened

370
00:25:15,974 --> 00:25:18,477
By the same fate
as Krypton's.

371
00:25:18,477 --> 00:25:21,480
The earth
is too primitive.

372
00:25:21,480 --> 00:25:23,482
You can flee
to new worlds

373
00:25:23,482 --> 00:25:25,984
Where war is
long forgotten.

374
00:25:26,485 --> 00:25:27,986
If you teach
the earth

375
00:25:28,487 --> 00:25:30,989
To put its fate
in any one man,

376
00:25:30,989 --> 00:25:32,491
Even yourself,

377
00:25:32,991 --> 00:25:35,494
You're teaching them
to be betrayed.

378
00:25:38,497 --> 00:25:39,498
Betrayed.

379
00:25:39,998 --> 00:25:40,999
Betrayed.

380
00:25:41,500 --> 00:25:42,501
Betrayed!

381
00:25:43,001 --> 00:25:44,419
Betrayed!

382
00:25:47,047 --> 00:25:49,550
And because
the summit has failed,

383
00:25:50,050 --> 00:25:51,552
We have no choice

384
00:25:52,052 --> 00:25:55,556
But to strive
to be second to none

385
00:25:56,056 --> 00:25:58,559
In the nuclear arms race.

386
00:25:59,059 --> 00:26:00,561
To that end,

387
00:26:01,061 --> 00:26:04,064
This administration
has pursued,

388
00:26:04,565 --> 00:26:06,567
And will continue
to pursue...

389
00:26:09,570 --> 00:26:11,572
Therefore--

390
00:26:14,575 --> 00:26:16,577
Just a minute.

391
00:26:20,080 --> 00:26:21,081
Lois.

392
00:26:21,582 --> 00:26:23,083
There you are!
What happened?

393
00:26:23,584 --> 00:26:25,085
What do you mean?

394
00:26:25,586 --> 00:26:28,088
"Meet me at 6:00 for
the press awards.

395
00:26:28,589 --> 00:26:29,590
Wear something
really nice

396
00:26:29,590 --> 00:26:31,091
And don't be late."

397
00:26:31,592 --> 00:26:33,594
Were we discussing
some other lois?

398
00:26:34,094 --> 00:26:35,596
I'm sorry.
I completely forgot.

399
00:26:36,096 --> 00:26:38,098
OK, get dressed,
and we'll go.

400
00:26:38,599 --> 00:26:41,101
I'D rather not,
if you don't mind.

401
00:26:41,602 --> 00:26:43,103
I've got thinking to do,

402
00:26:43,604 --> 00:26:45,606
But you go ahead, OK?

403
00:26:48,108 --> 00:26:49,109
Clark...

404
00:26:49,109 --> 00:26:52,112
Something's wrong,
isn't it?

405
00:26:53,113 --> 00:26:54,114
Hmm?

406
00:26:55,115 --> 00:26:57,618
Is there anything
I can do?

407
00:26:58,118 --> 00:27:00,120
Yes, as a matter
of fact.

408
00:27:00,621 --> 00:27:03,123
Could we get
some fresh air?

409
00:27:05,125 --> 00:27:07,127
Fresh air?

410
00:27:07,127 --> 00:27:08,128
Fresh air.

411
00:27:08,629 --> 00:27:11,632
Fresh air! Sure!
Sure, Clark. Sure.

412
00:27:11,632 --> 00:27:13,634
Who needs rubber chicken
and speeches anyway?

413
00:27:13,634 --> 00:27:16,637
Come on, let's get
some fresh air.

414
00:27:16,637 --> 00:27:18,639
Breathe really deep.

415
00:27:18,639 --> 00:27:21,642
Breathe.
Do you feel better?

416
00:27:21,642 --> 00:27:24,645
Clark? Clark! Clark!
Things aren't that bad!

417
00:27:24,645 --> 00:27:27,648
Clark, stop!
Oh, Clark!

418
00:27:27,648 --> 00:27:29,650
Clark! Clark!

419
00:27:39,159 --> 00:27:40,661
Superman!

420
00:28:00,180 --> 00:28:01,682
You OK?

421
00:28:01,682 --> 00:28:02,683
Great.

422
00:28:13,193 --> 00:28:15,696
Hey, look at that.

423
00:28:25,706 --> 00:28:28,709
Ready? There you
go! Bye-bye!

424
00:28:58,238 --> 00:29:00,240
How'd you like
going solo?

425
00:29:00,240 --> 00:29:01,742
I loved it...

426
00:29:01,742 --> 00:29:04,745
But not as much
as being with you.

427
00:29:04,745 --> 00:29:07,748
I needed to be
with you, too.

428
00:29:07,748 --> 00:29:09,750
You make me laugh.

429
00:29:11,251 --> 00:29:14,254
You're the only one
I can talk to.

430
00:29:14,254 --> 00:29:18,258
Sometimes, I don't know
what I'm supposed to do.

431
00:29:18,258 --> 00:29:20,761
I'm always
here for you.

432
00:29:20,761 --> 00:29:22,262
You know that.

433
00:29:22,262 --> 00:29:24,264
You'll do
the right thing,

434
00:29:24,264 --> 00:29:26,266
No matter
what it is.

435
00:29:26,266 --> 00:29:27,768
You always have.

436
00:29:27,768 --> 00:29:29,269
Thank you.

437
00:29:29,269 --> 00:29:31,271
You know something?

438
00:29:31,271 --> 00:29:32,272
What?

439
00:29:32,272 --> 00:29:34,775
You don't even
know my name.

440
00:29:34,775 --> 00:29:36,276
Kal-El.

441
00:29:38,278 --> 00:29:40,280
You remember,
don't you?

442
00:29:41,782 --> 00:29:43,283
I remember
everything.

443
00:29:43,283 --> 00:29:46,787
"Never set one of them
above the rest.

444
00:29:46,787 --> 00:29:48,789
Love all humanity
instead."

445
00:29:51,291 --> 00:29:53,293
That's not fair.

446
00:30:19,820 --> 00:30:20,821
Lois.

447
00:30:20,821 --> 00:30:23,824
Time to go.
We'll be late.

448
00:30:23,824 --> 00:30:25,325
Huh?

449
00:30:25,325 --> 00:30:29,830
What am I doing out here
freezing my butt off?

450
00:30:29,830 --> 00:30:32,833
Oh, you wanted
some fresh air.

451
00:30:32,833 --> 00:30:33,834
That's OK.

452
00:30:33,834 --> 00:30:36,336
I don't want
to catch a cold.

453
00:30:36,336 --> 00:30:38,338
I feel kind of weird.

454
00:30:38,338 --> 00:30:41,842
I feel like
I have jet lag.

455
00:30:41,842 --> 00:30:42,843
Jeepers.

456
00:30:42,843 --> 00:30:44,344
Isn't that crazy?

457
00:30:44,344 --> 00:30:45,345
Yeah.

458
00:30:45,345 --> 00:30:47,848
How about you?
You still down?

459
00:30:47,848 --> 00:30:49,850
Nope. Things are
pretty clear.

460
00:30:49,850 --> 00:30:53,854
Good. Too much thinking
wears down your batteries.

461
00:30:55,856 --> 00:30:59,359
Clark, you got to
go with your gut.

462
00:30:59,359 --> 00:31:00,360
Mmm.

463
00:31:00,360 --> 00:31:01,862
Come on.

464
00:31:07,159 --> 00:31:08,660
OK, here you go,
jeremy.

465
00:31:09,161 --> 00:31:11,163
Mr. Warfield
wants shots of you

466
00:31:11,663 --> 00:31:13,165
With lots
of local color.

467
00:31:13,665 --> 00:31:15,667
I can't find
anything special.

468
00:31:15,667 --> 00:31:16,668
Hi, jeremy.

469
00:31:17,169 --> 00:31:18,670
Superman!

470
00:31:18,670 --> 00:31:19,671
Jimmy.

471
00:31:20,172 --> 00:31:21,673
What a scoop!

472
00:31:21,673 --> 00:31:23,675
Want to take
a walk with me?

473
00:31:24,176 --> 00:31:25,677
Sure! OK!

474
00:31:26,178 --> 00:31:28,180
Jimmy, come on.

475
00:31:41,193 --> 00:31:43,195
You can't!
You'll get towed!

476
00:31:43,695 --> 00:31:46,698
Do you know what
a ticket costs here?

477
00:31:46,698 --> 00:31:48,700
Lacy, it's only money!

478
00:31:57,209 --> 00:31:59,711
Wait for me upstairs
in the gallery.

479
00:32:00,212 --> 00:32:01,213
Sure. OK.

480
00:32:01,713 --> 00:32:02,714
Good luck,
Superman.

481
00:32:03,215 --> 00:32:04,716
Thanks.

482
00:32:12,224 --> 00:32:15,227
I saved you a seat.

483
00:32:16,228 --> 00:32:17,729
Yay!

484
00:32:19,731 --> 00:32:21,233
All right, Superman!

485
00:32:23,235 --> 00:32:25,237
Madame secretary, I don't
represent any country,

486
00:32:25,237 --> 00:32:27,739
But I'd like
to address the delegates.

487
00:32:27,739 --> 00:32:31,743
In that case,
you will need a sponsor.

488
00:32:33,245 --> 00:32:35,747
I believe that will do.

489
00:32:35,747 --> 00:32:36,748
Please.

490
00:32:40,752 --> 00:32:42,254
Thank you.

491
00:32:44,256 --> 00:32:45,757
What's he going to say?

492
00:32:45,757 --> 00:32:48,260
Something wonderful.

493
00:32:48,260 --> 00:32:50,262
Madam secretary,

494
00:32:50,262 --> 00:32:52,764
Honorable delegates,

495
00:32:52,764 --> 00:32:54,766
Ladies and gentlemen.

496
00:32:55,267 --> 00:32:56,768
For many years now,

497
00:32:56,768 --> 00:32:59,771
I've lived among you
as a visitor.

498
00:32:59,771 --> 00:33:02,274
I've seen the beauty
of your many cultures.

499
00:33:02,274 --> 00:33:06,778
I've felt great joy in your
magnificent accomplishments.

500
00:33:06,778 --> 00:33:10,282
I've also seen
the folly of your wars.

501
00:33:10,282 --> 00:33:12,284
As of today, I'm not
a visitor anymore

502
00:33:12,284 --> 00:33:17,289
Because the earth
is my home, too.

503
00:33:17,289 --> 00:33:18,290
We can't live in fear.

504
00:33:18,790 --> 00:33:22,294
I can't stand idly by
and watch us

505
00:33:22,294 --> 00:33:25,797
Stumble into the madness
of possible nuclear destruction.

506
00:33:26,298 --> 00:33:28,300
And so,
I've come to a decision.

507
00:33:28,300 --> 00:33:32,304
I'll do what our governments
haven't done.

508
00:33:32,304 --> 00:33:33,805
Effective immediately,

509
00:33:33,805 --> 00:33:37,309
I'll rid our planet
of all nuclear weapons.

510
00:33:37,309 --> 00:33:39,311
Yay!
Yay!

511
00:33:39,311 --> 00:33:42,314
Yay, Superman.

512
00:33:44,316 --> 00:33:46,318
Way to go, Superman!

513
00:33:51,323 --> 00:33:53,825
Superman!

514
00:34:03,043 --> 00:34:05,546
Missile test alpha.
All systems go.

515
00:34:05,546 --> 00:34:08,549
4, 3, 2, 1.

516
00:35:57,783 --> 00:35:58,784
Oh! Hello!

517
00:35:58,784 --> 00:36:00,786
Nice to see you guys!

518
00:36:03,288 --> 00:36:05,791
Why don't you
just relax there?

519
00:36:05,791 --> 00:36:08,293
I'll get on with
the introductions.

520
00:36:08,293 --> 00:36:09,795
Dixie...

521
00:36:09,795 --> 00:36:11,296
And Trixie.

522
00:36:13,799 --> 00:36:17,803
From the land of the free
and the great cost overrun,

523
00:36:17,803 --> 00:36:19,805
Harry howler,
nuclear strategist

524
00:36:19,805 --> 00:36:21,807
From America's
top think tank

525
00:36:22,307 --> 00:36:24,810
And a great warmonger
in his own right.

526
00:36:24,810 --> 00:36:27,312
A hearty bienvenue
to Jean Pierre Dubois,

527
00:36:27,813 --> 00:36:30,816
Nuclear warhead dealer
to the world.

528
00:36:31,316 --> 00:36:32,317
His motto is,

529
00:36:32,317 --> 00:36:35,320
"If you didn't
buy it from Jean Pierre,

530
00:36:35,320 --> 00:36:38,824
You didn't buy it
on ze black market."

531
00:36:38,824 --> 00:36:40,325
General Romoff.

532
00:36:40,325 --> 00:36:44,830
A lot of people think of you
as the mad Russian.

533
00:36:44,830 --> 00:36:49,334
I like to think of you
as just madly eccentric.

534
00:36:49,334 --> 00:36:50,836
