00:53:13,485 --> 00:53:15,487
Isn't that
the doorbell?

807
00:53:16,488 --> 00:53:17,489
Yes.

808
00:53:34,006 --> 00:53:35,507
Lacy.

809
00:53:37,009 --> 00:53:38,010
Where's Clark?

810
00:53:38,510 --> 00:53:39,511
Well, the elevator--

811
00:53:40,012 --> 00:53:42,014
Never mind.
It's a long story.

812
00:53:42,514 --> 00:53:45,017
It always is
with Clark.

813
00:53:46,518 --> 00:53:48,520
Oh, great,
that's him!

814
00:53:50,022 --> 00:53:51,023
Clark?

815
00:53:51,523 --> 00:53:54,026
Hi. Those bellboys should
look where they're going.

816
00:53:54,526 --> 00:53:55,527
Superman?

817
00:53:56,028 --> 00:53:57,029
Superman?

818
00:53:57,529 --> 00:53:59,531
Is dinner ready?
Can we eat?

819
00:54:00,032 --> 00:54:01,533
Yeah.
Let's go sit down.

820
00:54:02,034 --> 00:54:03,535
Oh, great.

821
00:54:06,038 --> 00:54:07,539
Ohhh! Sorry!
Oh, dear.

822
00:54:08,040 --> 00:54:09,541
Oh, no, that's OK.

823
00:54:10,042 --> 00:54:11,543
Just leave it
there, Clark.

824
00:54:12,044 --> 00:54:14,046
Let me
just get a rag.

825
00:54:14,546 --> 00:54:15,881
Be right back.

826
00:54:19,468 --> 00:54:20,969
Where's Clark?

827
00:54:23,972 --> 00:54:25,974
Lex:?? Hello, dolly??

828
00:54:25,974 --> 00:54:27,476
?? Hello, dolly??

829
00:54:27,976 --> 00:54:31,480
?? It's so nice to have
me back where I belong??

830
00:54:32,981 --> 00:54:34,483
Don't be concerned,
blue boy.

831
00:54:34,983 --> 00:54:35,984
Only you can hear me.

832
00:54:36,485 --> 00:54:37,986
It's my own
private frequency.

833
00:54:37,986 --> 00:54:39,488
You might
call this lex TV.

834
00:54:39,488 --> 00:54:43,492
Look to your left,
tall, dark, and handsome.

835
00:54:43,492 --> 00:54:46,495
I'll blow 20 stories
off that building...

836
00:54:46,495 --> 00:54:49,998
Give or take
a floor or two. Peace.

837
00:54:51,500 --> 00:54:52,501
Men.

838
00:54:52,501 --> 00:54:55,504
I hope Clark's OK.
I better look.

839
00:54:55,504 --> 00:54:56,505
OK.

840
00:54:59,508 --> 00:55:00,509
I'm sorry.

841
00:55:00,509 --> 00:55:02,010
An emergency's
come up.

842
00:55:02,010 --> 00:55:04,012
My apologies
to miss Warfield.

843
00:55:04,012 --> 00:55:05,514
Oh, but--

844
00:55:05,514 --> 00:55:06,515
Superman!

845
00:55:07,015 --> 00:55:08,016
Take me with you!

846
00:55:08,016 --> 00:55:11,019
I could
cover the story!

847
00:55:11,019 --> 00:55:13,021
Have you seen Clark?
Huh?

848
00:55:21,530 --> 00:55:23,031
Guess who.

849
00:55:23,031 --> 00:55:25,534
It's your old friend lex.

850
00:55:27,035 --> 00:55:29,037
If you'd
planted a bomb,

851
00:55:29,037 --> 00:55:32,040
You'd be miles
from here by now.

852
00:55:32,040 --> 00:55:34,042
This is my nephew Lenny.

853
00:55:34,543 --> 00:55:35,544
He worships me.

854
00:55:36,044 --> 00:55:37,546
The dude of steel.

855
00:55:38,046 --> 00:55:40,048
Boy, are you
gonna get it!

856
00:55:40,549 --> 00:55:44,553
Silly me, thinking
I could fool the super guy.

857
00:55:44,553 --> 00:55:48,056
You're right. No bomb.

858
00:55:48,056 --> 00:55:49,057
It's just
that you're so involved

859
00:55:49,558 --> 00:55:51,059
In this world peace bit,

860
00:55:51,560 --> 00:55:54,062
You don't have time
for social calls.

861
00:55:54,563 --> 00:55:55,564
I confess.

862
00:55:56,064 --> 00:55:57,566
I tricked you.

863
00:55:57,566 --> 00:55:59,067
You look great.

864
00:55:59,568 --> 00:56:02,571
Enough small talk.
What are you up to?

865
00:56:02,571 --> 00:56:05,073
You know,
you're a workaholic.

866
00:56:05,574 --> 00:56:08,577
You're playing a good guy
24 hours a day.

867
00:56:09,077 --> 00:56:11,580
Why don't you stop
and smell the roses?

868
00:56:12,080 --> 00:56:14,583
Get yourself a pet--
a kitten, a puppy.

869
00:56:15,083 --> 00:56:16,585
You hate children
and animals.

870
00:56:17,085 --> 00:56:19,087
Why are you
in Metropolis?

871
00:56:19,087 --> 00:56:23,592
I want to introduce you
to the new kid on the block.

872
00:56:37,105 --> 00:56:39,107
Look closely at
the cell structure.

873
00:56:39,608 --> 00:56:42,110
You see
anything familiar?

874
00:56:42,110 --> 00:56:45,113
You've already broken
all the laws of man.

875
00:56:45,614 --> 00:56:48,116
Now you've broken
the laws of nature, too.

876
00:56:48,617 --> 00:56:51,119
You must have
hidden a device

877
00:56:51,119 --> 00:56:53,622
On a missile
I hurled into the sun.

878
00:56:53,622 --> 00:56:57,125
You know, Mr. Muscle,
I'll miss our chats.

879
00:56:57,125 --> 00:57:00,128
You're the only one
that could keep up with me.

880
00:57:00,128 --> 00:57:01,129
Lenny!

881
00:57:01,129 --> 00:57:03,131
What?

882
00:57:03,632 --> 00:57:05,634
I want to
propose a toast.

883
00:57:06,134 --> 00:57:07,636
To a nice guy...

884
00:57:08,136 --> 00:57:10,639
Who's about
to finish last.

885
00:57:11,139 --> 00:57:13,141
Arrr!

886
00:57:14,142 --> 00:57:15,644
Destroy Superman!

887
00:57:15,644 --> 00:57:17,145
Later.

888
00:57:17,145 --> 00:57:19,147
He's a little bit
anxious.

889
00:57:19,648 --> 00:57:20,649
Can you blame him?

890
00:57:20,649 --> 00:57:24,653
Not one of
your great thinkers.

891
00:57:24,653 --> 00:57:27,656
But I, in all modesty, am.

892
00:57:27,656 --> 00:57:29,658
The touching thing
about this plan

893
00:57:29,658 --> 00:57:32,160
Is you helped me devise it.

894
00:57:32,160 --> 00:57:35,163
Prison twisted your mind
into a delusionary state.

895
00:57:35,163 --> 00:57:37,666
No, no, no. Listen.

896
00:57:38,166 --> 00:57:40,669
I escaped from prison
with one thing on my mind--

897
00:57:41,170 --> 00:57:43,172
The end of Superman.

898
00:57:43,172 --> 00:57:46,175
So there I was,
the first time ever

899
00:57:46,175 --> 00:57:48,677
That I didn't
have a long-range,

900
00:57:48,677 --> 00:57:50,679
Truly devious
criminal scheme.

901
00:57:50,679 --> 00:57:53,682
And then
I came up with it.

902
00:57:53,682 --> 00:57:55,184
With this guy

903
00:57:55,184 --> 00:57:56,685
And you gone,

904
00:57:56,685 --> 00:57:59,688
I'll make a fortune
rearming the world.

905
00:57:59,688 --> 00:58:03,192
You'd risk nuclear war
for your financial gain?

906
00:58:03,192 --> 00:58:05,194
Nobody wants war.

907
00:58:05,194 --> 00:58:08,197
I just want to keep 
the threat alive.

908
00:58:10,199 --> 00:58:12,201
Nifty, huh?

909
00:58:17,080 --> 00:58:19,166
Good night,
sweet prince.

910
00:58:20,667 --> 00:58:22,669
Parting is...

911
00:58:22,669 --> 00:58:24,171
Inevitable.

912
00:58:25,172 --> 00:58:27,674
Destroy Superman!

913
00:58:27,674 --> 00:58:30,177
First, I have fun.

914
00:58:50,197 --> 00:58:51,198
Aah!

915
00:59:31,238 --> 00:59:32,739
Aah!

916
00:59:34,241 --> 00:59:35,742
Help me!

917
00:59:44,751 --> 00:59:45,752
Thank you, Superman.

918
01:01:08,836 --> 01:01:10,838
Santa Maria...

919
01:01:57,885 --> 01:01:59,887
Oh!

920
01:01:59,887 --> 01:02:01,889
Oh!

921
01:02:01,889 --> 01:02:03,891
Un gran miracolo.
Grazie.

922
01:02:22,117 --> 01:02:24,620
Eeyi! Hah!

923
01:02:24,620 --> 01:02:26,622
Aah!

924
01:03:47,202 --> 01:03:50,205
Aah!

925
01:04:08,724 --> 01:04:10,726
Oh!

926
01:04:32,247 --> 01:04:34,249
Arrrgh!

927
01:04:40,756 --> 01:04:41,757
Arrrgh!

928
01:04:53,769 --> 01:04:56,271
Aah!

929
01:05:06,782 --> 01:05:08,784
Yaaa!

930
01:05:21,213 --> 01:05:21,839
I said I'd get you

931
01:05:22,339 --> 01:05:25,342
To run one
of our papers yourself,

932
01:05:25,843 --> 01:05:27,344
And I meant it.

933
01:05:27,845 --> 01:05:29,346
Congratulations,
miss publisher.

934
01:05:29,847 --> 01:05:33,350
Thank you, daddy.
That's very nice.

935
01:05:33,350 --> 01:05:35,352
Step into
your office.

936
01:05:37,354 --> 01:05:39,356
Where'd this
come from?

937
01:05:39,356 --> 01:05:41,358
Oh, somebody
brought it in.

938
01:05:41,358 --> 01:05:43,360
We bought it cheap.

939
01:05:43,360 --> 01:05:46,864
OK. This time you have
both gone too far.

940
01:05:46,864 --> 01:05:49,867
You can print your rag
without lois lane.

941
01:05:53,370 --> 01:05:56,373
And you certainly have
no right to this.

942
01:05:56,373 --> 01:05:58,375
Lois, I'm sorry.

943
01:05:58,375 --> 01:06:00,377
Oh, let her go, 
darling.

944
01:06:00,377 --> 01:06:02,379
I mean,
she's useless.

945
01:06:02,379 --> 01:06:05,382
And while you're at it,
fire that Clark Kent.

946
01:06:05,382 --> 01:06:07,384
He hasn't been around
or even telephoned.

947
01:06:07,384 --> 01:06:09,887
I know. I'm worried.

948
01:06:09,887 --> 01:06:12,389
Oh, kitten,

949
01:06:12,389 --> 01:06:14,391
Didn't we have
our little talk

950
01:06:14,391 --> 01:06:15,893
About personal
involvement

951
01:06:15,893 --> 01:06:16,894
With the help?

952
01:06:16,894 --> 01:06:18,896
Now that you're 
the publisher--

953
01:06:19,396 --> 01:06:20,397
Daddy...

954
01:06:20,397 --> 01:06:21,398
Yes, darling?

955
01:06:21,398 --> 01:06:22,399
Stuff it!

956
01:06:24,902 --> 01:06:26,904
Lois?
Lois, I'm sorry.

957
01:06:26,904 --> 01:06:30,908
I promise you I had
nothing to do with that.

958
01:06:36,914 --> 01:06:38,916
Have you heard
from Clark?

959
01:06:42,920 --> 01:06:44,421
No.

960
01:07:08,445 --> 01:07:10,447
Just a minute.

961
01:07:10,447 --> 01:07:13,450
Oh, lois. What are
you doing here?

962
01:07:13,450 --> 01:07:15,452
I knew it.

963
01:07:15,452 --> 01:07:16,453
Oh, I've just,

964
01:07:16,453 --> 01:07:18,455
Uh...just got
a really bad flu.

965
01:07:18,455 --> 01:07:19,456
What do you mean
you knew it?

966
01:07:19,456 --> 01:07:20,958
How'd you know?

967
01:07:23,460 --> 01:07:24,461
You haven't been to work.

968
01:07:24,461 --> 01:07:26,463
You haven't called
the office.

969
01:07:26,463 --> 01:07:27,965
You haven't even
called me back.

970
01:07:28,465 --> 01:07:30,467
How could you not
call me back?

971
01:07:32,970 --> 01:07:34,972
Whatever it is,

972
01:07:34,972 --> 01:07:36,974
I guess you've
got your reasons,

973
01:07:36,974 --> 01:07:41,478
But I knew you
were here, you know?

974
01:07:42,479 --> 01:07:43,981
Somehow...

975
01:07:43,981 --> 01:07:45,983
Somehow something
pulled me here.

976
01:07:45,983 --> 01:07:48,986
I always know when
Superman's in trouble.

977
01:07:48,986 --> 01:07:51,989
Ha ha! Superman?
Something's happened to him?

978
01:07:52,489 --> 01:07:54,491
Everybody's saying
he's dead, but...

979
01:07:54,491 --> 01:07:57,494
It can't be true.
I just know it.

980
01:07:57,494 --> 01:07:59,997
I feel it in my heart.

981
01:07:59,997 --> 01:08:02,499
I think
he just needs help.

982
01:08:02,499 --> 01:08:06,503
Well, wherever he is, lois, 
I'm sure he'll manage.

983
01:08:06,503 --> 01:08:09,506
Well, if he can't...

984
01:08:09,506 --> 01:08:11,508
Manage...

985
01:08:11,508 --> 01:08:14,011
And he really is...
In trouble,

986
01:08:14,011 --> 01:08:15,512
Then there's, uh...

987
01:08:15,512 --> 01:08:19,016
There's a few things
I'd like to tell him.

988
01:08:21,018 --> 01:08:23,020
I'D tell him...

989
01:08:23,020 --> 01:08:26,523
That I will always
cherish the time

990
01:08:26,523 --> 01:08:28,525
We spent together,

991
01:08:28,525 --> 01:08:31,528
And I never expected
anything in return

992
01:08:31,528 --> 01:08:35,532
And no matter how few
minutes I saw him for,

993
01:08:35,532 --> 01:08:37,534
It always made me happy.

994
01:08:37,534 --> 01:08:42,039
And I would tell him...
That I love him,

995
01:08:42,039 --> 01:08:45,542
And that
I'll always love him,

996
01:08:45,542 --> 01:08:48,045
And that...whatever...

997
01:08:48,545 --> 01:08:50,547
Happens to the world, I...

998
01:08:50,547 --> 01:08:52,549
I know that...

999
01:08:52,549 --> 01:08:57,054
That he's doing his best
to make sure

1000
01:08:57,054 --> 01:08:59,556
That it'll be all right
for the rest of us.

1001
01:08:59,556 --> 01:09:02,059
Well, wherever he is,
lois,

1002
01:09:02,059 --> 01:09:04,061
I know that...

1003
01:09:04,061 --> 01:09:06,563
He would want
to thank you.

1004
01:09:12,569 --> 01:09:14,571
Listen, I'm, um...

1005
01:09:14,571 --> 01:09:16,073
I'm pretty tired,
you know,

1006
01:09:16,573 --> 01:09:18,575
So I think I'll 
just rest here

1007
01:09:18,575 --> 01:09:20,077
For a while, OK?

1008
01:09:20,077 --> 01:09:23,580
I'll be fine.
It's OK.

1009
01:09:24,081 --> 01:09:25,082
Please?

1010
01:09:28,085 --> 01:09:30,087
Well, I hope you
feel better, Clark.

1011
01:09:30,087 --> 01:09:33,090
Thanks.

1012
01:09:39,596 --> 01:09:41,098
Um...

1013
01:09:41,098 --> 01:09:44,101
If...if you do
see him,

1014
01:09:44,101 --> 01:09:47,104
Um...or--or--or
hear from him,

1015
01:09:47,104 --> 01:09:50,607
He might need this.

1016
01:09:57,531 --> 01:10:00,200
Oh, lex,
we're all very pleased

1017
01:10:00,200 --> 01:10:05,706
At all the nuclear missiles
and arms you've helped us sell,

1018
01:10:05,706 --> 01:10:09,710
And, uh, we've decided
to increase your commission.

1019
01:10:09,710 --> 01:10:13,213
Oh, guys, really,
that's great.

1020
01:10:13,213 --> 01:10:15,716
It's the least
we could do.

1021
01:10:15,716 --> 01:10:17,718
Well, I have
another idea.

1022
01:10:17,718 --> 01:10:20,721
Gentlemen, I've decided

1023
01:10:20,721 --> 01:10:23,223
To assume control
of the company.

1024
01:10:30,230 --> 01:10:33,734
My first official act
is to say, "you're fired!"

1025
01:10:35,235 --> 01:10:37,237
You're mad.

1026
01:10:37,237 --> 01:10:40,240
Oh, really?
Look at this.

1027
01:10:48,248 --> 01:10:51,251
If you want
a reference for work,

1028
01:10:51,251 --> 01:10:53,253
Forget it!

1029
01:10:56,256 --> 01:10:58,258
That was a good bit.

1030
01:10:58,258 --> 01:11:00,761
You know,
with my brains

1031
01:11:00,761 --> 01:11:04,264
And your...
Frankly, your brawn,

1032
01:11:04,264 --> 01:11:07,267
The possibilities
are absolutely staggering.

1033
01:11:07,267 --> 01:11:09,770
I could be president,
emperor, king.

1034
01:11:09,770 --> 01:11:12,773
Did you see how scared
those guys were?

1035
01:11:12,773 --> 01:11:15,275
And what
do you fear?

1036
01:11:15,275 --> 01:11:17,277
What? Now?

1037
01:11:17,277 --> 01:11:19,780
With Superman dead,
and you're on my team?

1038
01:11:19,780 --> 01:11:21,782
It's like I'm the coach,

1039
01:11:21,782 --> 01:11:24,284
And you're the best
power forward ever.

1040
01:11:24,284 --> 01:11:25,285
What's to fear?

1041
01:11:38,799 --> 01:11:41,802
All that remains
of Krypton's energy

1042
01:11:41,802 --> 01:11:43,804
Is yours.

1043
01:11:43,804 --> 01:11:45,806
After it is gone,

1044
01:11:45,806 --> 01:11:49,810
You will belong solely
to your new home.

1045
01:11:50,811 --> 01:11:55,315
If our dying planet
can save your life, my son,

1046
01:11:55,315 --> 01:11:58,819
We have not died
in vain.

1047
01:12:43,989 --> 01:12:46,491
Rrraaarr!

1048
01:13:05,010 --> 01:13:06,011
Where is the woman?

1049
01:13:06,512 --> 01:13:08,013
You'll never find her.

1050
01:13:08,013 --> 01:13:12,017
If you will not tell me,
I will hurt people.

1051
01:13:18,524 --> 01:13:20,526
Rooaarr!

1052
01:13:20,526 --> 01:13:24,029
Yaaaah!

1053
01:13:25,030 --> 01:13:28,033
Rooaarr!

1054
01:13:33,539 --> 01:13:35,541
Stop! Don't do it!
The people!

1055
01:13:42,548 --> 01:13:43,549
Aah!

1056
01:13:47,553 --> 01:13:49,555
Yaaahh!

1057
01:14:14,079 --> 01:14:15,581
Ohhh!

1058
01:14:29,595 --> 01:14:31,597
Easy, now, easy.

1059
01:14:31,597 --> 01:14:33,599
Slow, slow, slow.

1060
01:14:33,599 --> 01:14:35,601
Stop! That's enough!

1061
01:14:35,601 --> 01:14:37,603
That's enough.

1062
01:14:37,603 --> 01:14:39,605
You win.
I'll take you to her.

1063
01:14:52,034 --> 01:14:53,535
Raaarrgh!

1064
01:14:55,537 --> 01:14:56,538
Yaahh!

1065
01:14:57,039 --> 01:14:59,041
Rooaarr!

1066
01:15:11,053 --> 01:15:13,055
Where is she?

1067
01:15:13,055 --> 01:15:14,056
Far away from here
and safe.

1068
01:15:14,056 --> 01:15:16,558
Don't go in there.
She's not in there.

1069
01:15:22,064 --> 01:15:26,068
Ah...aahh...

1070
01:16:50,152 --> 01:16:52,654
Errr!

1071
01:16:58,660 --> 01:17:03,165
Errrr!

1072
01:17:03,165 --> 01:17:06,168
Raarrr!

1073
01:17:52,714 --> 01:17:56,718
Grrrrr!

1074
01:17:57,219 --> 01:17:58,720
Aah!

1075
01:17:58,720 --> 01:18:01,223
Uugh!

1076
01:18:03,725 --> 01:18:05,227
Aah!

1077
01:18:23,745 --> 01:18:26,748
Aaaahhh!

1078
01:18:31,753 --> 01:18:35,257
Aaarrrrgh!

1079
01:18:35,257 --> 01:18:38,260
Rrrarrrr!

1080
01:19:17,216 --> 01:19:19,927
We've got to tone down
these headlines.

1081
01:19:19,927 --> 01:19:21,428
Tone down our headlines?

1082
01:19:21,428 --> 01:19:23,931
Lacy, that's all
the common man reads.

1083
01:19:23,931 --> 01:19:26,433
We could do with
less sensationalism.

1084
01:19:26,433 --> 01:19:28,936
Less sensational papers
go broke.

1085
01:19:29,436 --> 01:19:30,938
I taught you long ago

1086
01:19:31,438 --> 01:19:33,941
That the business of
newspapers is business.

1087
01:19:34,441 --> 01:19:34,942
No, daddy.

1088
01:19:35,442 --> 01:19:36,443
Our business
is journalism.

1089
01:19:36,944 --> 01:19:38,445
We can't be
so irresponsible.

1090
01:19:38,946 --> 01:19:39,446
Otherwise,

1091
01:19:39,947 --> 01:19:41,448
We'll lead everyone
into a disaster.

1092
01:19:41,949 --> 01:19:43,450
Don't be overdramatic.

1093
01:19:43,450 --> 01:19:45,452
What kind of disaster

1094
01:19:45,452 --> 01:19:47,454
Could we possibly
bring about?

1095
01:19:47,955 --> 01:19:49,957
Raaaarr!

1096
01:19:49,957 --> 01:19:51,458
Lacy!

1097
01:20:32,499 --> 01:20:35,502
Aaahh...

1098
01:20:36,503 --> 01:20:37,504
Oh!

1099
01:21:24,051 --> 01:21:26,053
What's going on?

1100
01:21:42,069 --> 01:21:43,570
Are you sure
you know

1101
01:21:43,570 --> 01:21:45,072
What you're doing,
Mr. White?

1102
01:21:45,072 --> 01:21:46,073
Well...

1103
01:21:46,073 --> 01:21:48,075
Uh...ahem.

1104
01:21:48,075 --> 01:21:50,077
Here comes
Mr. Warfield.

1105
01:21:50,077 --> 01:21:53,080
You'd better have
an explanation, white,

1106
01:21:53,080 --> 01:21:55,582
Or you'll talk
to your lawyers from jail.

1107
01:21:56,083 --> 01:21:58,085
You know, I'm not a tycoon.

1108
01:21:58,085 --> 01:22:00,087
I'm just
an old reporter,

1109
01:22:00,087 --> 01:22:03,090
But I've read enough
in my own newspaper

1110
01:22:03,090 --> 01:22:05,592
About hostile takeovers
of big companies,

1111
01:22:05,592 --> 01:22:07,594
And you, Mr. Warfield,

1112
01:22:07,594 --> 01:22:09,096
Must have been
asleep at the wheel,

1113
01:22:09,596 --> 01:22:12,599
Because I convinced
the bankers of this city

1114
01:22:12,599 --> 01:22:15,102
That our Daily Planet
should be treated

1115
01:22:15,102 --> 01:22:19,106
Like a natural resource,
protected from predators,

1116
01:22:19,106 --> 01:22:21,108
So I convinced them
to lend me the money.

1117
01:22:21,108 --> 01:22:23,610
I bought up
the outstanding shares,

1118
01:22:23,610 --> 01:22:28,115
And you, Mr. Warfield, are
now a minority shareholder.

1119
01:22:29,116 --> 01:22:30,617
Everyone back to work.

1120
01:22:30,617 --> 01:22:32,619
Way to go,
chief!

1121
01:22:32,619 --> 01:22:35,122
Ha ha ha ha ha! 
Yay!

1122
01:22:35,122 --> 01:22:36,123
I'm sorry.

1123
01:22:36,123 --> 01:22:38,125
You win some,
you lose some.

1124
01:22:38,125 --> 01:22:41,128
Now, this is what
I call a newspaper.

1125
01:22:41,128 --> 01:22:43,130
Compliments of
the Daily Planet.

1126
01:22:43,130 --> 01:22:45,132
Have a nice day!

1127
01:22:45,132 --> 01:22:46,633
We did it!
We're back!

1128
01:22:49,636 --> 01:22:51,638
Hi, everybody.
Am I late?

1129
01:22:51,638 --> 01:22:53,640
Hey, Mr. Kent.
No, he's not here yet.

1130
01:22:53,640 --> 01:22:55,142
It must have been
an effort for you

1131
01:22:55,142 --> 01:22:57,144
To drag yourself
out of bed this morning.

1132
01:22:57,144 --> 01:22:59,146
I'm feeling better.

1133
01:22:59,146 --> 01:23:00,647
Had a visit from
a good nurse.

1134
01:23:00,647 --> 01:23:02,149
It must have been some
pretty good medicine,

1135
01:23:02,649 --> 01:23:04,151
Because miss lane said
you were really ill.

1136
01:23:04,651 --> 01:23:06,153
Jimmy, sometimes
all you need

1137
01:23:06,153 --> 01:23:07,154
Is some
loving attention

1138
01:23:07,654 --> 01:23:08,655
From the right
person.

1139
01:23:08,655 --> 01:23:10,157
Glad you're back,
Clark...

1140
01:23:10,157 --> 01:23:11,658
And remember...

1141
01:23:11,658 --> 01:23:13,660
I am covering
Superman's press conference.

1142
01:23:13,660 --> 01:23:15,662
You just tape
crowd reactions.

1143
01:23:15,662 --> 01:23:17,664
Reactions, OK.

1144
01:23:17,664 --> 01:23:19,166
Oh, dear.

1145
01:23:19,166 --> 01:23:20,667
Guess I'll need 
a tape recorder.

1146
01:23:20,667 --> 01:23:21,668
Be right back.

1147
01:23:21,668 --> 01:23:23,170
Clark.

1148
01:23:23,170 --> 01:23:26,173
Same old Mr. Kent.
He'll never change.

1149
01:23:26,173 --> 01:23:28,175
I hope not.

1150
01:23:28,175 --> 01:23:29,676
Whoo!

1151
01:23:35,182 --> 01:23:36,683
Hi, Superman.

1152
01:23:36,683 --> 01:23:39,186
Lois, good
to see you again.

1153
01:23:39,186 --> 01:23:41,188
Good to see you, too.

1154
01:23:41,188 --> 01:23:42,689
Morning, gentlemen.

1155
01:23:42,689 --> 01:23:44,191
Excuse me.

1156
01:23:44,191 --> 01:23:45,692
Thank you.

1157
01:23:45,692 --> 01:23:48,195
We've survived
the threat of war

1158
01:23:48,195 --> 01:23:50,197
And found
a fragile peace.

1159
01:23:50,197 --> 01:23:53,700
I thought I could give
you freedom from war.

1160
01:23:53,700 --> 01:23:56,703
I was wrong.
It's not mine to give.

1161
01:23:58,205 --> 01:24:00,207
We're still
a young planet.

1162
01:24:00,207 --> 01:24:02,209
There are galaxies
out there,

1163
01:24:02,209 --> 01:24:04,711
Other civilizations
for us to meet,

1164
01:24:04,711 --> 01:24:07,714
To learn from.

1165
01:24:07,714 --> 01:24:10,217
What a brilliant future 
we could have.

1166
01:24:10,217 --> 01:24:12,219
And there will be peace

1167
01:24:12,219 --> 01:24:15,222
When the world's people 
want it so badly

1168
01:24:15,222 --> 01:24:19,226
That their governments will
have to give it to them.

1169
01:24:19,226 --> 01:24:23,730
I wish you could see
the earth as I do.

1170
01:24:23,730 --> 01:24:27,234
When you really see it, 
it's just one world.

1171
01:24:31,071 --> 01:24:32,573
Think he'll find us?

1172
01:24:32,573 --> 01:24:36,577
Never. We'll lay low
for a while,

1173
01:24:36,577 --> 01:24:38,078
Couple of years.

1174
01:24:38,078 --> 01:24:41,081
I'll come up
with a new plan.

1175
01:24:41,081 --> 01:24:44,084
Whoa. Good thing
I brought my drums.

1176
01:24:54,094 --> 01:24:55,596
Oh, no!

1177
01:24:57,097 --> 01:24:59,600
Uncle lex,
you won't believe this,

1178
01:24:59,600 --> 01:25:01,101
But it's...

1179
01:25:01,101 --> 01:25:02,102
Superman.
Superman.

1180
01:25:02,102 --> 01:25:04,104
Oh, wow!

1181
01:25:04,104 --> 01:25:05,105
Oh, wow!

1182
01:25:05,105 --> 01:25:09,610
Hey, this rocks! Hey!

1183
01:25:09,610 --> 01:25:11,111
Morning, father.

1184
01:25:11,111 --> 01:25:12,613
Lenny's been under
a bad influence.

1185
01:25:12,613 --> 01:25:13,614
Think you can help him?

1186
01:25:13,614 --> 01:25:15,616
Every boy
can be helped.

1187
01:25:15,616 --> 01:25:17,618
I think you're right.
Good luck, son.

1188
01:25:17,618 --> 01:25:18,619
Come with me,
my friend.

1189
01:25:18,619 --> 01:25:21,121
Do you have 
a drum set?

1190
01:25:21,121 --> 01:25:24,625
Hey! Mozart's back!

1191
01:25:28,629 --> 01:25:30,130
Dwayne,
mozart's back!

1192
01:25:30,130 --> 01:25:32,132
I see him, Bubba!

1193
01:25:34,134 --> 01:25:35,636
Shut up!

1194
01:25:37,137 --> 01:25:38,138
Marshal,
take him away.

1195
01:25:38,138 --> 01:25:39,139
Thank you kindly,
Superman.

1196
01:25:39,139 --> 01:25:40,140
Come on, Luthor.

1197
01:25:40,140 --> 01:25:42,643
One thing--
how'd you beat him?

1198
01:25:42,643 --> 01:25:44,144
High school physics.

1199
01:25:44,645 --> 01:25:46,647
I figured
that if your creature

1200
01:25:46,647 --> 01:25:48,649
Was born from the sun,

1201
01:25:48,649 --> 01:25:50,651
That was
his energy source.

1202
01:25:50,651 --> 01:25:52,152
Will the world
be vaporized?

1203
01:25:52,152 --> 01:25:53,654
No, Luthor.

1204
01:25:53,654 --> 01:25:55,155
As always,
it's on the brink,

1205
01:25:55,155 --> 01:25:57,157
With good fighting evil.

1206
01:25:57,157 --> 01:25:58,659
See you in 20.
